From an Initial Appraisal of this film, a copy of which is in Folder 13, Box 17:
                Events during the Fall Semester (about 10 minutes); Homecoming parade in Durham;
                Alumni Reunion and Barbecue; Residential quads with homecoming signs and displays;
                Duke-Georgia Tech football game; Boxing match; Duke-NCSU baseball game; Spring on
                the campus (lead-in to Centennial); The Centennial Weekend, Apr. 21-23, 1939 (about
                15 minutes); Friday:; Reception of delegates, H. M. Wriston speaks; Dedication of
                the Sarah P. Duke Gardens, band concert; Saturday a.m.: Education and the public;
                Trustees of Duke University and Duke Endowment; President Few introduces J. M.
                Finley (?); Speech by Edouard Benes; Saturday p.m.: The University and the Nation;
                Speakers; Dean Wannamaker introduces P. H. Hanes; P. F. Hanes hands packet to
                President Few to be opened in 100 years; Sunday a.m.:; Chapel Service; Portrait of
                the celebrants; Audience for Carillon concert by Anton Brees; Year-end ceremonies
                (about 5 minutes); May Day Pageant, The Woman's College; The 87th Commencement:;
                Representatives of orphanages preparing to lay wreath on JBD's tomb; Alumni
                registration and luncheon; Commencement ceremony; Family groups receiving degrees
                (twins, mother-daughter); Honorary degree recipients; Lowering of the flag;
                Reference Copy: VHS. UA88-57-14; Reference Copy: DVD. UA88-57-14
